- AGENTS.md: §Output Style (no stdout/stderr, use structured tracing)
- asupersync_plan_v4.md: §4 (I6: Determinism is first-class)
- asupersync_v4_formal_semantics.md: §1.8 (Observable labels)

## Acceptance Criteria
- Provides a structured trace event type set covering spawn/complete/cancel/reserve/resolve/finalize/tick.
- Core runtime emits trace events only via `Cx::trace` (no stdout/stderr).
- Trace capture is deterministic and replay/diff friendly.
- Tests can dump formatted traces on failure without requiring global logging crates.
